      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/136/26",
      "text": [
        " «أَمَّا فِي اَلْهَدْيِ فَلاَ وَ أَمَّا فِي اَلْأَضْحَى فَنَعَمْ وَ يُجْزِي اَلْهَدْيُ عَنِ اَلْأُضْحِيَّةِ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3067 - Muhammad al-Halabi asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a group of people—does a cow suffice for them?\nImam (as) replied: \"As for the hady (sacrificial offering for Hajj), no. But as for the sacrifice (Udhiyah), yes. And the hady suffices in place of the sacrifice.\""
        ]
      }
    },
